TL;DR (Plain Language Summary)
------------------------------

What you CAN do:
- Install and use buddymon personally on your own machines
- Use it internally at your company, as long as you do not monetize it
- Modify buddymon for yourself privately (including building new features)
- Share the software privately with friends (USB stick, direct message, etc.)
- Use it for education, learning, teaching, and research
- Show buddymon in your portfolio, on your resume, or in job interviews
- Stream or record videos with buddymon, as long as you visibly credit
  "powered by buddymon by Marcel Bich"
- Archive buddymon at archive.org, Software Heritage, or the Wayback Machine
- Read and study the source code

What you CANNOT do:
- Sell it, monetize it, or build a paid product or paid support business around it
- Redistribute it on package managers (PyPI, Homebrew, apt, etc.) - only the
  Official Repository holder (currently: Marcel Bich) or others with his
  explicit written permission may do that
- Build a competing product derived from this code
- Use this code as input or training data for any AI system (for training,
  fine-tuning, analysis, indexing, or cloning)
- Remove the attribution notice

Plus: This License automatically converts to the MIT License if Marcel Bich is
inactive on the Official Repository for 24 consecutive months, or upon his death.


1. Definitions
--------------

"Software" means buddymon, including all source code, object code, documentation,
configuration files, assets, and other materials distributed under this License.

"Copyright Holder" means Marcel Bich, the original author of the Software.

"You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising permissions
granted by this License.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, in whole or in part, that is
intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation,
including but not limited to selling copies, offering paid services based on the
Software, or incorporating the Software into a paid product.

"Competing Product" means any software product or service that substantially
replicates, reimplements, or substitutes the functionality of the Software and
that is offered to third parties (whether commercially or free of charge).

"AI Systems" means machine learning models, artificial intelligence systems,
large language models, neural networks, automated code generation tools, AI
agents, AI assistants, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems, embedding
models, and any other automated systems that learn from, analyze, or generate
content based on input data.

"Official Repository" means the public git repository hosted at
https://github.com/Marcel-Bich/buddymon, or any successor repository officially
designated by the Copyright Holder.


2. Grant of Rights
------------------

Subject to the terms and restrictions of this License, the Copyright Holder
hereby grants You a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to:

(a) Download and install the Software on Your own systems.

(b) Use the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes.

(c) Use the Software internally within Your organization, provided that such
    use is not monetized and does not generate direct or indirect revenue.

(d) Modify the Software for Your own private use, including the development of
    new features, provided that such modifications remain private and are not
    redistributed.

(e) Share the Software privately with friends and family through direct
    person-to-person channels (such as USB drives, email, or direct messages),
    provided that such sharing does not constitute public redistribution.

(f) Conduct security research on the Software, provided that any discovered
    vulnerabilities are disclosed responsibly to the Copyright Holder before
    public disclosure.

(g) Use the Software for educational purposes, including teaching, learning,
    coursework, and academic research.

(h) Reference and demonstrate the Software in Your professional portfolio,
    resume, or during job interviews.

(i) Create and publish streaming content, video recordings, screencasts, and
    similar media that include the Software, provided that visible attribution
    "powered by buddymon by Marcel Bich" is displayed in or alongside such content.

(j) Submit copies of the Software to historical archives such as archive.org,
    Software Heritage, and the Wayback Machine for preservation purposes.

(k) Study the source code of the Software for the purpose of learning and
    understanding.


3. Restrictions
---------------

The following actions are expressly prohibited under this License:

(a) No Direct Monetization. You may not sell, license, sublicense, rent, lease,
    or otherwise commercially distribute the Software. You may not offer the
    Software as a paid service, paid software-as-a-service (SaaS) offering, or
