(d) No Public Forks Presenting Themselves as Official. You may not publish
    public modifications or forks of the Software in a manner that presents
    them as the official version, as endorsed by the Copyright Holder, or as
    affiliated with the original project.

(e) No AI Use (Strict). The Software may not be used, in whole or in part, as
    input, training data, fine-tuning data, reference material, context, or
    retrieval corpus for any AI System. This explicitly includes:

    - AI agents that read or analyze the source code
    - AI assistants that have the source code in their context window
    - RAG systems indexing the source code
    - Embedding models generating vectors from the source code
    - Any attempt to reconstruct, reimplement, or clone the functionality of
