7. Dead Man's Switch (Automatic Conversion to MIT)
--------------------------------------------------

This License automatically converts to the MIT License upon the occurrence of
either of the following Triggering Events:

(a) Death of the Copyright Holder, as evidenced by a death certificate or an
    authoritative written declaration by a legal successor; or

(b) Inactivity: If no commit authored by Marcel Bich (git identifier:
    43651076+Marcel-Bich@users.noreply.github.com) appears in the git history
    of the Official Repository (https://github.com/Marcel-Bich/buddymon) for
    24 consecutive months.

Fallback: If the Official Repository becomes unavailable, Inactivity is
measured from the last known public commit by Marcel Bich on any public git
hosting service, or from a written declaration by a legal successor.

Manual Override: The Copyright Holder may at any time manually convert this
License to the MIT License by publishing a written declaration. Upon the death
of the Copyright Holder, any legal successor may do the same.

Version-Specific Parameters: Each version of the Software has its own LICENSE
file with its own inactivity duration and parameters. Older versions retain
their original rules even if newer versions of the Software use different
parameters.

Upon conversion, all restrictions in this License (including the AI clause in
Section 3(e) and the Attribution Requirement in Section 4) no longer apply, and
the Software falls under the standard terms of the MIT License.


